Condition : 4 - Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved drawings, the development hereby permitted shall not progress beyond damp proof course level, until samples of the materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces noted below are made available to view on site, and agreed in writing by, the local planning authority:
a). facing materials for the building, including brickwork detail;
b).windows/ doors (including detailed sections at metric scale 1:20 through all external reveals on each of the elevations) ;
c). boundary fencing
The development shall be carried out in accordance with the details so agreed and shall be retained as such thereafter.
REASON: To ensure that the development is carried out to the highest standards of architecture and materials.
